nt; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" alt="" style="left: -80px;"> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><div style="clear:both;"></div></ul></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) left top no-repeat; display: block;"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) right top no-repeat; display: block;"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>The popularity of this model among brides is because it reflects almost all following fashion trends:</strong></p><ul><li>a delicate elastic top with embroidery;</li><li>a built-in bra or cut-off cups;</li><li>a tender silhouette of a lace dress;</li><li>an open back and a short lacing on air loops;</li><li>and a full detachable skirt with a train.</li></ul><p><strong>This course contains a lot of couture techniques. I will show you the following:</strong></p><ul><li>how to seamlessly cover the corset with lace;</li><li>how to join a lace folded skirt to a dress, so that you don’t have any extra thickness and the transition from a corset to a dress is smooth and invisible;</li><li>how to sew an elastic top between a face and a lining;</li><li>how to make a lining with built-in cups.</li></ul><p><strong>The special feature of the course is tambour (luneville) sequin embroidery.</strong></p><p>The process of cutting, sewing and decoration of a garment from scratch to final operations is described and illustrated in detail.<br> All necessary patterns and bonuses (for printing) are attached as follows:</p><ul><li>2 tables for AUTOMATIC pattern adjustments calculation for all patterns of this course;</li><li>patterns of a corset face and a corset lining;</li><li>patterns of decorative details.</li></ul><div><p><strong>The aim of the course</strong>&nbsp;is my great desire to teach the techniques of making such dresses. All the techniques can be used in various combinations, so that you can sew different models of evening, cocktail, prom and wedding dresses.</p><p><strong>The course is useful</strong>&nbsp;both to beginners as well as to experienced professionals in making wedding and evening dresses. It can be handy for dressmaking atelier personnel as a professional development training.</p></div><div></div><div><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;6h 45m</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-24-framing-the-fabric-for-embroidery/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-24-framing-the-fabric-for-embroidery/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-12-03T21:03:36+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-12-03T21:03:36+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 24. Framing the fabric for embroidery."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 24. Framing the fabric for embroidery."><meta itemprop="description" content="I start framing our bobbinet fabric. The piece is rather wide and I need to be really careful. fabric perpendicular to raw edge of woolen fabric on the first bar"><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Dress with Detachable Full Skirt. Part 1."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding dress with detachable full skirt. part 1., video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 24. Framing the fabric for embroidery.</h1><p><strong>I start framing our bobbinet fabric.</strong> The piece is rather wide and I need to be really careful.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image002.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I join one edge of bobbinet fabric perpendicular to raw edge of woolen fabric on the first bar. I baste it with wide plain stitches with waxed coarse thread and thick needle. </strong>I make a bar tack at the beginning and there is no need to do it at the end of stitch, a back stitch will do.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image004.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image006.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>It is desirable that bobbinet fabric is rectangular </strong>to place it between bars without any distortion.</p><p><strong>I fold fabric from the second side, which will be sewn, move the second symmetrical bar and place it parallel to the first bar with the joined bobbinet fabric. </strong>I ensure that the edges of bars aligned.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image008.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image010.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image012.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image014.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I spread fabric that its edges are perpendicular to the bars. I pin the bobbinet fabric to both sides of woolen fabric on the second bar and in the middle. </strong>The fabric should be flat without distortion and creases.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image016.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image018.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image020.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image022.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I join the pinned side of bobbinet fabric with hand stitches. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image024.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I turn the bars with the sewn bobbinet fabric face up.</strong></p><p>The strips of woolen fabric are placed over bobbinet fabric.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image026.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I put a perpendicular part of the frame and fix it with a screw at the end of the slot. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image028.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Similarly I fix the second bar from the other side of the construction. I also screw through the beginning of the slot.&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image030.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I join the bottom of the first vertical bar with the horizontal one with the screw in the slot. I do not screw tight, so that the bars can move. </strong>I try to make a right angle between the bars as it is important.<strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image032.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image034.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I do the same </strong>with the second part of the lower horizontal bar, so that our construction is solid.</p><p><strong>And now, I pull the right edge of the horizontal bar down to achieve bouncy tension of the mesh.</strong> I pull the bar to the level until the bobbinet fabric stretches like a drum, tighten the screw and fix the horizontal bar in this position.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image036.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I fix the distance between the screw and the end of the slot on the vertical bar. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image038.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I pull the bottom horizontal bar from the second edge, about, approximately, the same distance from the bottom of the slot of the second vertical bar.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image040.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>So, the horizontal thread of the bobbinet fabric is good and the fabric is perfectly stretched, but there is almost no tension along the edges of the bobbinet fabric.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image042.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>Therefore, now the task is to stretch the bobbinet fabric in two sides along the edges. </strong>I will use a durable tape, for example, reps and pins. In this case I prefer patchwork pins to ordinary tailor pins.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image044.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Patchwork pins are long, thin and sharp pins with flat heads. </strong>They are most suitable for framing as there is less mesh tear and they are easy to work with.</p><p><strong>I fix a tape on a woolen fabric.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image046.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>I get the tape over the bar, take it through between the bar and the fabric edge and pin the pulled bobbinet fabric to the tape. </strong></p><p><strong>Important advice:</strong> when you go along the first edge of the fabric, there is no need to make a hard tension, you just need a slight tension and the hardest tension should be applied to opposite side or the opposite raw edge.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image048.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image049.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Again I throw the tape across the bar, tighten it, passing through the gap between the bar and the edge of the bobbinet fabric, I pin, after stretching the fabric to the tape, again I throw the tape across the bar, pulling the edge of the fabric and so on. </strong></p><p><strong>Try to put the pins horizontally, </strong>using the maximally possible width of the tape.</p><p>.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image051.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image053.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image055.png" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2024.files/image057.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I reach the end of the bar and similarly stretch the bobbinet fabric along the second edge, achieving its tension.</strong></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format. To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose&nbsp;<strong>“print in actual size”</strong>. In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Automatic Pattern Alterations Calculator:</strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGcorset/corset.htm" target="_blank">The Dress (Corset)</a></strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGskirt/ENGskirt.htm" target="_blank">The Skirt</a></strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/belt%2C%20bow.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Belf and The Bow</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20front.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Front</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20lining.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Lining</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/pattern.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Pattern</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/skirt.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Skirt</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/top.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Top</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>


